body:
It is tricker to provide a sum() operation in Streamlet directly because the operation only works for specific types. In this PR, a few standard reducers are added for users to make it simple to implement sum.

Example:
instead of:
s.reduceByKey(x -> ..., x -> ..., (x, y) -> x + y);

user can do it like:
s.reduceByKey(x -> ..., x -> ..., StreamletReducers::sum);

Refactor grouping logic from BoltDeclarer functions to classes so that it is easier for them to be reused by Streamlet API, from calling different function

boltDeclarer.XGrouping(parent, streamId, ...);

to:

StreamGrouping grouper = new X(...);
boltDeclarer.grouping(parent, streamId, grouper);

- No logic change.
- Old functions are still available.
